1
00:00:24,065 --> 00:00:25,191
{\an8}[all shouting]

2
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:35,869
[laughing]

3
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:37,245
Advance.

4
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:41,207
[panting]

5
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:50,133
{\an8}Fear not, tiny friends,
for Sea Hawk is here!

6
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:52,218
[shouts]

7
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:57,724
Well, perhaps we should fear a little.

8
00:00:58,683 --> 00:00:59,517
Let's go!

9
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:04,939
[gasps]

10
00:01:05,398 --> 00:01:06,483
[powering up]

11
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:12,238
-Hang on!
-Huh?

12
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:15,950
[shouts]

13
00:01:18,203 --> 00:01:19,120
[grunting]

14
00:01:21,039 --> 00:01:22,665
Netossa, this is the last of them!

15
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:23,583
Sound the--

16
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,168
Wait. Where's Sea Hawk?

17
00:01:26,336 --> 00:01:27,170
[groans]

18
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:29,255
[groans]

19
00:01:30,006 --> 00:01:30,965
Adventure?

20
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,008
[Sea Hawk grunts]

21
00:01:32,091 --> 00:01:34,344
Okay. Now sound the retreat.

22
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:41,518
[sighs]

23
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,019
[sea elf 1 crying]

24
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:47,941
[sea elf 2 crying]

25
00:01:51,402 --> 00:01:52,362
[gasps]

26
00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:58,284
Hmm.

27
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:00,703
I'll be back for you.

28
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:04,833
<i>♪ We're on the edge of greatness ♪</i>

29
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:07,961
<i>♪ Turning darkness to light ♪</i>

30
00:02:09,045 --> 00:02:10,755
<i>♪ We're right beside you ♪</i>

31
00:02:10,839 --> 00:02:12,132
<i>♪ Ready to fight ♪</i>

32
00:02:13,550 --> 00:02:16,052
<i>♪ We're gonna win in the end ♪</i>

33
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:17,512
<i>♪ We must be strong ♪</i>

34
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:19,389
<i>♪ And we must be brave ♪</i>

35
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:21,224
<i>♪ We must be brave ♪</i>

36
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:27,605
<i>♪ We gotta find every bit of strength</i>
<i>That we have and never let it go ♪</i>

37
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:29,482
<i>♪ We must be strong ♪</i>

38
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:36,573
I know it's been tough going
with losing Salineas,

39
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:38,992
but we're picking up the pieces.

40
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:41,035
I'm sure we can turn this around.

41
00:02:41,452 --> 00:02:43,454
I mean, we captured Double Trouble.

42
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:46,833
They're refusing to talk to us, but still.

43
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:48,710
So, uh...

44
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:50,086
-Swift Wind.
-Hm?

45
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:52,630
You just got back
from scouting the Southern Coast.

46
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:54,007
What does it look like?

47
00:02:54,173 --> 00:02:55,383
On fire!

48
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:57,760
Anything more specific?

49
00:02:58,678 --> 00:03:00,513
On lots of fire.

50
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:02,223
Okay...

51
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:03,433
Adora.

52
00:03:03,516 --> 00:03:05,560
You came from Plumeria,
what's their status?

53
00:03:05,643 --> 00:03:06,477
Any good news?

54
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:09,314
Perfuma is securing the Whispering Woods,

55
00:03:09,397 --> 00:03:12,108
and Frosta reports her kingdom
has not been breached.

56
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:13,693
-Great.
-Yet.

57
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:15,486
But the Horde's working on it.

58
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:17,572
Day and night. Nonstop.

59
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:21,409
Well, that is okay.

60
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:24,954
Because Sea Hawk, Spinnerella
and Netossa just saved everyone

61
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,205
in Sea Elf Village.

62
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,374
With, uh, Glimmer.

63
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:32,003
Who didn't tell us she was going,
but just kind of showed up.

64
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:35,798
Again? Glimmer,
you can't just keep going off on your own.

65
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:38,134
Hmm. Where have I heard that before?

66
00:03:38,217 --> 00:03:39,344
Oh, right.

67
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:42,722
When I stayed here to find the Horde spy
and Salineas fell.

68
00:03:42,805 --> 00:03:44,641
That's not fair. We didn't know.

69
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:48,102
-Tell that to Mermista.
-Hey, where is Mermista?

70
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:49,979
[Mermista groaning]

71
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:51,731
Oh, look.

72
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:52,690
More ice cream.

73
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:55,109
'Cause I'm the princess of ice cream now.

74
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:56,569
[chuckles]

75
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:02,242
She's, uh, taking some me time.

76
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:04,619
Me time. Great.

77
00:04:04,827 --> 00:04:06,204
We all could use some of that.

78
00:04:06,287 --> 00:04:08,665
So, let's check in with each other
more often,

79
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:10,416
and, Glimmer, if you could--

80
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,795
I'm not going to hide inside the castle
while our people are in danger.

81
00:04:14,003 --> 00:04:15,046
I'm the queen.

82
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,090
You don't give me orders.

83
00:04:17,173 --> 00:04:19,968
Okay. I get that you're upset, but--

84
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:21,636
Don't talk to Bow like that.

85
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:23,263
Adora, it's fine. Glimmer's just--

86
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:25,765
I need to stop the Horde, any way I can.

87
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:27,183
We're done for today.

88
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:30,270
Ugh. Fine.

89
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:33,106
Clearly we aren't going to get
anything done right now.

90
00:04:37,527 --> 00:04:38,444
[door slams]

91
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:40,530
All in all,
not the worst meeting we've had.

92
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,658
I've never seen Glimmer like this.

93
00:04:43,908 --> 00:04:44,951
Or Adora.

94
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,953
I just wish I knew how to help them.

95
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:49,247
Ah, don't blame yourself, lad.

96
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:52,834
Hey, you know, I just had an idea,
not preplanned at all.

97
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:55,586
Let's take a break
and have a boys' night out on the town!

98
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:56,671
[gasps]

99
00:04:56,754 --> 00:04:57,880
Can I come, too?

100
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:01,134
I should really stay here
in case Glimmer and Adora need me.

101
00:05:01,217 --> 00:05:02,385
One night off won't hurt.

102
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:03,803
What do you say?

103
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:07,056
[Swift Wind] Boys' night out.
Boys' night out.

104
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:09,600
Boys' night out! Boys' night out!

105
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,269
Why am I the only one doing this?

106
00:05:11,352 --> 00:05:12,937
You know what? Why not?

107
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:14,063
Grand!

108
00:05:14,147 --> 00:05:16,649
And then my brilliant secret plan
can begin.

109
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:18,067
-What's that?
-Nothing.

110
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:21,404
Forward to a friendship adventure!

111
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:26,451
[Catra] Lord Hordak.

112
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:28,995
Sounds like congratulations are in order.

113
00:05:29,078 --> 00:05:30,413
[Hordak] Yes.

114
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:32,957
The princesses are in utter disarray,

115
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,917
abandoning territory,

116
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:38,212
scattering before us
like the cowards they are.

117
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:41,966
We're crushing them.
Once you return to the Fright Zone,

118
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:44,510
I'll march our troops
on the rest of the coastal towns.

119
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:47,680
No. Now that Horde Prime's arrival
is imminent,

120
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:50,600
I shall remain in the field
to ensure victory.

121
00:05:50,683 --> 00:05:56,481
Besides, out of all the princesses,
Entrapta has yet to face me on the field.

122
00:05:56,981 --> 00:05:57,982
[Hordak laughing]

123
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:02,653
And what exactly am I supposed to do
while you remain in the field?

124
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:05,239
Whatever I deem necessary to win.

125
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:08,951
Return to your post in the Fright Zone
and await my orders.

126
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:12,955
Soon, all of Etheria will be at my feet.

127
00:06:17,126 --> 00:06:18,086
[sighs]

128
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:22,256
Force Captain Octavia,
have you finished your perimeter?

129
00:06:22,799 --> 00:06:24,675
[Octavia] <i>We're doing the final sweep.</i>

130
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:28,262
Excellent. Double Trouble
should be breaking radio silence soon.

131
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:30,056
They'll have new coordinates for you.

132
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:32,475
Force Captain Scorpia, come in.

133
00:06:32,558 --> 00:06:34,769
[Horde soldier] Watch out! [grunting]

134
00:06:35,269 --> 00:06:38,397
Aw, man. Even when he's winning,
Hordak is annoying.

135
00:06:38,481 --> 00:06:40,650
Now he suddenly loves fighting,

136
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:44,195
and I'm getting stuck
with whatever he deems necessary.

137
00:06:44,612 --> 00:06:47,490
[groans] Never thought I'd miss
shut-in Hordak.

138
00:06:47,698 --> 00:06:50,076
Meet me at the Sea Gate.
I wanna take a break anyway.

139
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,120
[medieval music playing]

140
00:06:52,203 --> 00:06:54,914
Sea Hawk,
I thought you said boys' night out.

141
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,707
It's the middle of day.

142
00:06:58,209 --> 00:07:00,670
New experiences!

143
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,296
Huzzah!

144
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:04,882
Day, night, it matters not.

145
00:07:05,174 --> 00:07:07,009
You're overdue for some levity.

146
00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:10,888
Last time I was here,
it was with Adora and Glimmer,

147
00:07:11,097 --> 00:07:12,765
and things were great.

148
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,350
Not like now.

149
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:15,685
It is true.

150
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:17,478
Things are looking dour.

151
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:18,521
[slurps]

152
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:20,356
This drink is...

153
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:22,650
-extra sour.
-[shrieks]

154
00:07:22,733 --> 00:07:24,610
Could be the Rebellion's...

155
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:25,778
[slurping]

156
00:07:25,862 --> 00:07:27,697
darkest hour.

157
00:07:30,408 --> 00:07:31,284
Nonsense!

158
00:07:31,367 --> 00:07:32,660
You know why?

159
00:07:32,743 --> 00:07:33,661
Hit it!

160
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,457
[squeeze box playing]

161
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:41,961
<i>♪ Oh, when the seas are rough and dire</i>
<i>We turn to friends and we conspire ♪</i>

162
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:45,089
<i>♪ To relight the sacred fire</i>
<i>Of rebellion ♪</i>

163
00:07:45,214 --> 00:07:48,801
<i>♪ When the Horde tightens the noose</i>
<i>Around our daring sea rescues ♪</i>

164
00:07:48,885 --> 00:07:51,804
<i>♪ We take some time</i>
<i>To cut loose from the Rebellion ♪</i>

165
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:55,183
<i>♪ Sure friends aren't seeing eye to eye ♪</i>

166
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:59,061
<i>♪ 'Tis no reason to curl up and die ♪</i>

167
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:02,648
<i>♪ Friendship just needs a resupply ♪</i>

168
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:06,319
<i>♪</i> [both]<i> Oh, it's fun</i>
<i>It's fun to be friends with friends ♪</i>

169
00:08:06,402 --> 00:08:10,865
<i>♪ Oh, it's fun</i>
<i>It's fun to be friends with friends ♪</i>

170
00:08:10,948 --> 00:08:14,702
<i>♪ And when Hordak hits us robotical</i>
<i>We'll respond with tunes most nautical ♪</i>

171
00:08:14,785 --> 00:08:16,245
<i>♪ And take a moment to... ♪</i>

172
00:08:16,454 --> 00:08:17,288
<i>♪ To ♪</i>

173
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:19,207
<i>♪ To-to-to-to, to-to... ♪</i>

174
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:20,333
<i>♪ Uh, to pop ♪</i>

175
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:24,253
<i>♪ Soda botticals ♪</i>

176
00:08:24,962 --> 00:08:25,922
[man coughing]

177
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,883
Oh, man. Third rhyme. Rough stuff.

178
00:08:29,675 --> 00:08:33,638
<i>♪ </i>[both]<i> Oh, how fun</i>
<i>How fun to be friends with friends ♪</i>

179
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:38,184
<i>♪ Oh, how fun</i>
<i>How fun to be friends with friends ♪</i>

180
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:41,687
<i>♪ Sometimes we'll fight, but that's okay</i>
<i>We'll work it out another day ♪</i>

181
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:44,982
<i>-♪ I know things'll work out in the end ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Oh, yes ♪</i>

182
00:08:45,066 --> 00:08:48,778
♪ [all] <i>'Cause it's fun</i>
<i>To be friends with friends ♪</i>

183
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:55,743
<i>♪ Oh, it's fun to be friends</i>
<i>With friends ♪</i>

184
00:08:55,826 --> 00:08:58,746
<i>♪ Friends with friends ♪</i>

185
00:09:01,832 --> 00:09:02,875
It's an ambush!

186
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:05,253
Whoo! Better! It's a kidnapping!

187
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:07,880
Sea Hawk, what are you doing?

188
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:11,300
Don't worry,
it's all part of my brilliant secret plan.

189
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:12,552
What plan?

190
00:09:12,635 --> 00:09:16,138
To unite the princesses
and cheer up my dearest Mermista.

191
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:18,015
They love rescuing people...

192
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:20,977
so I paid my friend Bill to kidnap us.

193
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:24,313
The ladies will put aside their problems
to rescue us,

194
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:25,773
go on a mission of fun,

195
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:28,734
and then it's a happy ending for all!

196
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:31,529
Wait, you paid them to-- [grunts]

197
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:34,615
<i>♪ The princesses will stop their fight ♪</i>

198
00:09:34,949 --> 00:09:37,618
<i>♪ When they save us, it'll be all right ♪</i>

199
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:42,498
<i>♪ We'll hang with Bill</i>
<i>The rest of the night ♪</i>

200
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:45,751
<i>♪ It's fun to be friends with friends ♪</i>

201
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,796
<i>♪ Sha-boombitty-boom-ba-boo ♪</i>

202
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:51,674
<i>♪ Hey, Bill, did you get taller? ♪</i>

203
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:54,927
<i>♪ And when did you get that scar? ♪</i>

204
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:59,348
You, uh, didn't have a scar.

205
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:02,977
This might not be Bill.

206
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:05,563
-No, this isn't Bill.
-What?

207
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:10,651
[screams]

208
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:17,867
What do we do?

209
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:20,161
We have to get a message to our friends.

210
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:23,706
Swift Wind, try to contact Adora
through your sacred bond.

211
00:10:23,789 --> 00:10:25,750
[chuckles] Yeah, yes. Yes.

212
00:10:25,875 --> 00:10:26,917
My plan can still work.

213
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:30,046
They'll just unite to rescue us
for real this time.

214
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:31,339
[laughing]

215
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:33,299
Nothing's spun out of control.

216
00:10:33,674 --> 00:10:35,509
Do your thing, noble steed.

217
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:36,552
[grunts]

218
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:38,220
Come on, Adora, pick up.

219
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:40,139
Pick up.

220
00:10:40,514 --> 00:10:41,891
[Swift Wind grunting]

221
00:10:42,892 --> 00:10:44,560
Mermista? Are you alone?

222
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,062
[Mermista] Totally.

223
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:48,397
[gasps]

224
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:50,608
[Glimmer clearing throat]

225
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:54,487
-I thought you said you were alone.
-I am.

226
00:10:54,737 --> 00:10:56,197
Deep down inside.

227
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:58,616
So alone.

228
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:02,536
Ugh. Are you two gonna fight again?
Whatever.

229
00:11:07,917 --> 00:11:12,004
I was just checking up on Mermista,
but clearly you have it covered.

230
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:17,968
Glimmer, what is going on with you?

231
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:20,596
I know things are bad right now,
but we can fix it.

232
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:23,682
Why is that always your answer
to everything?

233
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:26,352
Because it's the only thing we can do.

234
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:28,521
Things are worse than ever.

235
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:31,273
The Horde has Salineas,
the coast is falling.

236
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:33,359
We haven't fixed anything!

237
00:11:33,442 --> 00:11:36,821
That's why we need to work together
instead of you pushing us away,

238
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:39,115
and if you'd just listened to us
you'd know that,

239
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:40,991
and why can I hear the ocean right now?

240
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:43,869
Anything?

241
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:45,788
Ah. She hung up on me.

242
00:11:45,996 --> 00:11:47,832
But I could tell that she's in distress.

243
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:49,708
I should be at her side right now.

244
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:52,044
-Swift Wind, calm down.
-[grunting]

245
00:11:52,294 --> 00:11:54,797
It'll be okay. We'll figure something out.

246
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:56,215
Fear not.

247
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:59,176
I know how to get a message
to my sweet Mermista.

248
00:11:59,301 --> 00:12:03,431
After all, she taught me
how to speak seagull!

249
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:06,517
[cawing]

250
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:13,315
[squawking]

251
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,903
I may be a bit rusty.

252
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:19,822
