if you tell anyone this, but...

295
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:38,460
I thought winning would be different.

296
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:40,754
Or at least more...

297
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:43,257
I don't know. Fun?

298
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:44,842
[radio static]

299
00:14:46,343 --> 00:14:47,344
Come on.

300
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:49,930
You're not still mad about before,
are you?

301
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:54,518
Stop being so sensitive.
Get over it and talk to me, Scorpia.

302
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:56,854
Scorpia?

303
00:14:58,397 --> 00:14:59,231
Scorpia.

304
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:01,317
[grunting]

305
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:05,529
[grunting]

306
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:11,368
[Scurvy] Good news, boys.

307
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:15,998
Someone cared enough about you three
to pay a hefty ransom.

308
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,333
Yes! Yeah!

309
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,960
The princesses. Of course!

310
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,378
Just like I planned.

311
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:22,504
[Scurvy laughing]

312
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:30,220
All that very loud,
very public singing about the Rebellion,

313
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:33,557
and you think your ransom was paid
by the princesses?

314
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:34,975
[foghorn blowing]

315
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:37,227
The Horde controls the seas now,

316
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:40,981
and they're paying top dollar
for high-ranking rebel prisoners.

317
